The paper deals with signal processing and statistical analysis of stochastic processes, which are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of orthogonal transforms and independent-component analysis suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are likely sub-categories. The study of sparse processes and the comparison of different basis functions suggest that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the use of numerical optimization and statistical criteria suggests that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible sub-category as well.
